Hurricane Floyd, a Category 4 storm with 155 mph winds, surprised forecasters as it headed towards the Bahamas and threatened the Florida coast.
Evacuations were ordered in both areas.
FEMA prepositioned supplies in Atlanta to respond quickly.
Forecasters warned of heavy rains and flooding in Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands.
The storm's path remained uncertain, with potential impact along the East Coast.
As Floyd intensified, concerns grew over its potential impact on Florida.
Residents stocked up on supplies as the storm's trajectory remained unpredictable, causing widespread evacuations along the coast.
